Not as good as their other location because it’s older looking and not as bright but the jerk chicken, peas and rice and oxtail gravy were all great. Cabbage was way over cooked though. Rounded up from 3.5 stars because the other stuff was all above average.

Delicious Jamaican food at very reasonable prices. My wife and I have been enjoying their food for many years. I love, love, love their jerk chicken legs, oxtail, curry goat, chicken soup, rice and peas, sweet fried plantains and patties. My wife enjoys their fried fish and stewed chicken. The food is so good, it's almost addictive.
I got delivery and only got the food and not the drink I ordered. Jerk chicken was good but somewhat burnt and dry.
The best jerk chicken and rice and beans. Small drink variety. Very nice people behind the counter. Some seating area. Great prices. Cash and cards.
Love the small entrees. Get the curry chicken with jerk gravy.
tall guy is very rude, I think he has a problem, one tiny piece of chicken for $7 dollars give me a break, thats robbery

Excellent takeout restaurant for jamaican food. Food is always fresh. It’s always a short wait. Best during the day, they sometimes will run out of popular dishes by end of day. Great jerk chicken, curry goat, oxtail. You really can’t go wrong here for takeout. The prices are very reasonable. It’s right next to the subway, newkirk Avenue stop and parking is often available on the street.
Love this place but they NEVER have enough sweet plantains...so you can never get the complete meal.
One of the best places for AUTHENTIC Jamaican food! Love it here!
I love this food. And the old girl make me feel like I'm eating my grandmother food! This is better than delicious!! 💯✔
The closest West Indian (Jamaican) restaurant in the area...The curry is passable nothing like a good Trini curry thou...

This place needs to be shut down, they don't know how to grill chicken 0 grill marks, chicken tasted boiled and was very wet. I would give 0 starts if I could! DO NOT ORDER unless you are looking to lose your appetite
The food is good but they need customer service training and wear gloves when serving food; that's just sanitary.

I’ve been contemplating this place for a while and finally decided to try it. I’m glad I did. The oxtail was was just amazing. The rice and peas were cooked perfectly and went really well with the oxtail. The staff was friendly enough. Unlike the many negative reviews commenting on the poor customer service, I had a pleasant experience. I highly recommend it if you’re in mood for some Jamaican food or just want to try it for the first time.
Rice and peas nice as usual however fish and new staff not so like before.
Fantastic dinner for the price - very generous portions and really well done. The limeade is seriously good too
Good food
Customer service is horrible. Food was ok.

I brought 4 fish, rice & peas and got all the way home to only have 1 fish.  Then I called back and was told to come back however, I live 40 mins away.  Then I go back the next day and when I walk in THEY ALL STANDING AROUND LOOKING STUPID!! NO ONE EVEN APOLOGIZED!! Then to top it off I brought a small order of rice & peas and said to the cashier " YOU SHOULD JUST GIVE ME THIS FOR MY TROUBLES" she just looking at me.  WHAT A DAMN INCONVENIENCE THIS WAS TO COME BACK.  PEOPLE CHECK YOUR TAKE OUT ORDERS.  I won't be going back there anytime soon.
Delicious food.

Terrible just terrible!! I purchased oxtails and rice and peas one day and the oxtails weren't cooked properly I couldn't even bite a piece of the meat off that how hard it was. I could only eat the rice. Since then I never bought food from them again!
Great jerk chicken, and great prices
A great place to grab a meal or shop and near the subway.

Food is great, but customer service is a big NO NO....cashiers are very rude, everytime i go there i end up in a argument with the cashiers because of their disgusting attitude. If you do not like your job THEN QUIT!!!!!! Cause i come here and pay for my food and not beg so i expect to get the service that i am paying for and mind you there food is not cheap. Cashier forgot my item and now i have to waste another 15 min. Of my life to go back and deal with more attitudes. Fisher Mans Cove need to do better when it comes to customer service. Didnt even want to give you ppl a star. I do not tolerate disrespect when it comes to my mother and the cashier tried to disruspect her one day and lorddddd i lost it in there. Where do i even put in a complaint? Who is the manager? Customer service is HORRIBLE....worst location EVER!!!!!!!!! Dnt even want to go back to that place no more. You've lost a valuable customer, been coming since i was a kid with my parents and now im old enough with a kid to know right from wrong and the way your employees treat customers is wrong! Noone wants to be talked to any and which types of way. Very disturbing. Train your workers!!(especially the caramel skin girl, slim and tall) always have a attitude and is very very disruspectful) she through my change at me when i handed it to her.  I can go on and on but its not even worth it. I will be taking my business else where.

Yesterday afternoon 6/6/17 at the newkirk plaza location the lady at the counter/cashier had a bad and disruptive attitude, this isn't the first time. I'm finally tired of her attitude and having to deal with her non sense.  She doesnt answer your question, and when she does it is with a highly offensive attitude.  What was worse , was that she began to have a violent verbal argument with the nice driver.  She began cursing him out dirty in front of the other customers.  Business is not conducted this way, and she does not represent your business in a good light.  That woman needs to be reprimanded or let go!  I've been coming to fisherman cove for over 5 years loyally!  Outside of that the food is always great.  But the cashier left a bad taste in my mouth and spirit.

Customer service SUCKS! The staff there needs to get trained in speaking to customers, people are spending their monies not begging. Just asking for a paper bag you get attitude, why is that necessary. Come on . As a fellow Jamaican I can say, my country people do not know how to excel in customer service. The attitudes. Wow!
Their jerk chicken is consistently good.
Love the jerk chicken

I've been going here for years and always try to be nice to the cashier  as I place my order but she always has the most nastiest attitude ever. She has a brown complexion and always has her hair in a low ponytail. She always does the cashier at the Newkirk location. Today was the final straw for me. Her attitude was worst than ever and all I did was place and order and as she recited it back to me her tone was disgusting and rude. If she doesn't  like her job she should't work there because she makes the establishment look really  bad. I see why my friends stop coming to this location.everytime I leave this place my day is just ruined from her negative energy. That's not how customers should feel after leaving a business. I'll never return to this location I'll just try another location but for now I won't be supporting this business because how I felt today wasn't acceptable to me. I'm not for anyone losing their job but she has to go because everyone complains about her. Which is making fisherman cove look bad as a whole.

People remember if you're going to eat here the food is ok......smfh.......but the service is horrible I have never been to a place where your paying them but they treat you with no type of respect.....like they r giving me the food for free I wish I can give this place no stars but hey u have to..... smfh

Excellent, authentic, affordable and quick service with no BS... As others have commented the Jerk Chicken (their highlighted item) is not out-of-this-world but their stewed chicken and curry goat are second to none. TIP: they have AMAZING fried chicken that tastes like an old black grandma cooked it for you. However it is completely sold out by mid lunch hour. As far as value goes, where else in the city are you going to find a meal that has you stuffed until dinner time for $5.25 (lunch special)? This place is awesome in that regard... One caveat, they have "we deliver" plastered all over the place but they do NOT actually deliver.

The female staff lack customer service I've been going to this restaurant since it was on the other side of Newkirk Plaza and I have been ordering the same thing for years stew chicken and rice and peas all I ask for is white meat (chicken breast) never had a problem in the many years I've been going to this establishment but these new female staff are horrible and lazy she refuses to sell me any white meat chicken and claims there isn't any I go everyday just to see if she will finally give me what I ordered but its been two weeks now and she still refuses to give me my correct order so I just stopped going there all together

just order a medium curry goat from fisherman cove on newkirk plaza... i open my food up and there was a piece of hair on the goat. i called the restaurant back told them what was in my food and there response was that could be hair from the goat,... i will never order from there again. this is unacceptable. i know what human hair looks like....

I find the entire staff especially the women have a serious attitude....I don't know if they're over worked, not getting f*^ked or what.....I observed a male customer seemingly intimidated by the attitude of 1 of the servers when clarifying his order about wanting some cabbage on his jerk chicken....yes the food is good but the attitudes suck !!!  I say be grateful for the customer base that keeps you in the money because although you may play gospel music and may go to church on sunday, if your attitude sucks and you're not grateful to your customer base, that money can blow away like dust in the wind, I will defintely spread the word about them !

The food  is great but the service truly bad and needs to change.  The people who work there talk about the customer which I found to be extremely disrespectful. The most I hade to wait for food was 45 minutes and they started to serve people who got there after me I truly hope that  they change the way they treat people or they are going to loose a lot of business.
Great tasting food.
I love their food is the best in Brooklyn BUT they need to work on their attitude. If you don't like your job, you can always get a new one.
Tastes like home. Authentic Jamaican food.the jerk chicken plate is absolute perfection and won't break your pockets! Love it!
Love everything
Love going there to get some curry goat platter with rice & peas and cabbage. Sometimes I get oxtail & macaroni pie or soup.. but all their food is on point..no doubt about it.
The food is great but it runs out quickly....don't go there too late. Service kinda sucks

Went here today for some chicken soup and I was disappointed. I was lucky if I even got a bone included in the soup..the soup should be called broth and other stuff soup. ANYTHING but chicken. : (  Jerk chicken is okay nothing to come back to.
The food was great but the workers have a nasty attitude

In a word: Amazing.  I'm a huge fan of jerk chicken, and theirs is absolute perfection.  I haven't had anything other than the jerk chicken, with rice and beans, and some salad, but it's everything you expected to find.  Their sauces are fantastic, and the chicken is perfectly spiced, juicy, and absolutely wonderful.  Check it out - you won't be disappointed.
